LOCAL ward committee member elections got off to a rocky start in eThekwini on Sunday. At Ntuzuma H, people were turned away at the local hall. Busani Mbatha (48) told Daily Sun officials were only expecting 200 people, but there were many more and they locked the gates.&nbsp; Independent Councillor Thandanani Mabanga said he informed the municipality the hall was too small and said people were left confused. Municipal spokeswoman Tozi Mthethwa said 40 wards postponed the elections.&nbsp; Of 110 wards, only 70 voted successfully.&nbsp; &ldquo;Law enforcement will be increased so the elections are completed next Sunday.&rdquo;